\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line In the Evaluator\'E2\'80\'99s judgement\'2C the programme does not meet minimum standards in any of the relevant eight criteria.  Accordingly\'2C the overall recommendation is that the programme should not be accredited.\line \line The Evaluator\'E2\'80\'99s report is detailed and carefully referenced with respect to individual minimum standards.  These cannot be easily summarised.  However\'2C the major shortcomings of the programme fall into two categories\'3A\line \line \'28a\'29 Conceptualisation of the programme\line With respect to Programme Design \'28Criteria 1\'29\'2C the need for the degree is inadequately presented\'2C and there is no indication of deliberation and review with relevant external bodies.  Tourist growth is hypothesised.  At the level of the curriculum for a vocational programme such as this\'2C work-integrated learning is underdeveloped.  A scaffolded and sequential workplace guide accompanied by assessment criteria for work-based learning is not available.   With respect to Assessment \'28Criterion 6\'29\'2C module outlines provided are incomplete. Module design indicates little attention to assessment criteria.  The SAQA submission mistakes specified outcomes for assessment criteria.  The variety of assessment throughout the programme is limited to tests and assignments\'2C and the spread and number of assessments in the assessment plan is not consistent with module credits and scope of work across all modules. \line \line \'28b\'29 Capacity to offer the programme \line  The submission does not provide adequate evidence of capacity to offer the programme across all seven sites.  In particular\'2C this applies to Staffing \'28both Criteria 3 and 4\'29\'3B and Infrastructure and Library Services \'28Criterion 7\'29.   \line \line The Accreditation Directorate concurs with the Evaluator\'E2\'80\'99s judgements that the programme does not merit accreditation. \line \cell \pard 

