\intbl \ql 1. The rationale for the programme is based on anticipated growth in international and domestic tourism in South Africa. This should not constitute the primary basis for the training of high-level hospitality managers as tourism impacts on all sectors unevenly. \line \line Module outlines provided are incomplete as they indicate little attention to the level of required achievement in the outcome\'2C to the extent that many \'E2\'80\'98outlines\'E2\'80\'99 amount to statements of topics.  In some learning areas\'2C the progression of learning is not evident.  Consequently\'2C the purpose of the qualification is likely to be compromised. \cell \pard 
\intbl \ql Criteria 1 \cell \pard 

\intbl \row \pard 
\pard\trowd\trqc \trpaddl113\trpaddt113\trpaddb113\trpaddr113\trpaddfl3\trpaddft3\trpaddfb3\trpaddfr3\trgaph100\trrh100\trleft36
\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx7938
\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx9639

\intbl \ql 2. There is inadequate evidence that support and responsibility for the professional growth and development of the large contingent of part-time and independent contractors and support staff is available.\cell \pard 
\intbl \ql Criterion 3\cell \pard 

\intbl \row \pard 
\pard\trowd\trqc \trpaddl113\trpaddt113\trpaddb113\trpaddr113\trpaddfl3\trpaddft3\trpaddfb3\trpaddfr3\trgaph100\trrh100\trleft36
\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx7938
\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx9639

\intbl \ql 3. The programme assigns teaching responsibilities to a disproportionately small number of full-time academic staff.  This has the potential to compromise the quality of delivery at some sites.  It also limits the opportunity of part-time staff to debate and to become fully conversant with all relevant details of programme delivery and review meetings\'2C pedagogic practices\'2C modes of identifying and responding to students at risk\'2C and opportunity for one-on-one consultation. The latter are of particular importance in the light of the undemanding admission requirements for degree study.\line Information on the size and capacity of the cohort of administrative staff at sites of delivery is not available.\cell \pard 
\intbl \ql Criterion 4\cell \pard 

\intbl \row \pard 
\pard\trowd\trqc \trpaddl113\trpaddt113\trpaddb113\trpaddr113\trpaddfl3\trpaddft3\trpaddfb3\trpaddfr3\trgaph100\trrh100\trleft36
\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx7938
\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx9639

\intbl \ql 4.  Assessment tools and method choices are not informed and supported by either the purpose of particular forms of assessment or the criteria for successful achievement.  It is necessary that assessment criteria are accompanied by appropriate level descriptor\'28s\'29\'2C and aligned with delivery modes and available resources as well as the chosen assessment methods.\cell \pard 
\intbl \ql Criterion 6\cell \pard 

\intbl \row \pard 
\pard\trowd\trqc \trpaddl113\trpaddt113\trpaddb113\trpaddr113\trpaddfl3\trpaddft3\trpaddfb3\trpaddfr3\trgaph100\trrh100\trleft36
\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx7938
\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx9639

\intbl \ql 5. No assessment criteria can be identified for all modules in the application.  A case in point is the construction of work-based learning which provides experience without explicitly indicating how these experiences are linked to conceptual development.  Assessment criteria for work-based learning appear not to have been considered in Programme Design. Self-evaluation by students seems to be a main method of evaluation.\cell \pard 
\intbl \ql Criterion 6\cell \pard 

\intbl \row \pard 
\pard\trowd\trqc \trpaddl113\trpaddt113\trpaddb113\trpaddr113\trpaddfl3\trpaddft3\trpaddfb3\trpaddfr3\trgaph100\trrh100\trleft36
\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx7938
\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx9639

\intbl \ql 6. The availability and access to specialist venues for modules requiring food preparation\'2C food service and cocktail lounge\'2Fbar service are indeterminate. It is assumed the necessary facilities and equipment will become available upon approval of the programme. Therefore\'2C the capacity of such facilities to meet learning outcomes in these and related modules cannot be assessed. Accompanying foundational skills training\'2C practical handling and methods\'2C work practice and their assessment of competency are in need of such up-to-date venues. \line Equity in provision across all sites of delivery is not assured.  Provision is dependent on the size of student enrolments.\line \cell \pard 
